{"id": 231206462, "title": "The Best Things People Learned From Their Dads", "text": "1. \"My dad was a stay-at-home dad. My mom worked and made the money for our family. When we were kids, other moms never wanted to be around us because my dad always took me places while my mom worked. He took me to every birthday party, play date, and event when I was a kid, and later did the same for my siblings. But other moms never wanted to include my dad, and to an extent, myself and my siblings. As a result, my dad grew to feel insecure about his role as a stay-at-home parent, and my siblings and I grew up lacking social skills because other kids were discouraged from playing with us.\"", "summary": "<h1>\"But the first, best wisdom came from my dad, who counseled patience and a fresh insight.\"</h1><p><img src=\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2024-06/4/21/enhanced/456add1ee4e8/original-1783-1717535931-2.jpg?crop=1244:829;0,0\" /></p><hr /><p><a href=\"https://www.buzzfeed.com/michelelbird/flipped-lessons-from-dad\">View Entire Post &rsaquo;</a></p>", "url": "https://www.buzzfeed.com/michelelbird/flipped-lessons-from-dad", "image": "https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2024-06/4/20/campaign_images/ceed18319bef/here-are-the-best-things-people-ever-learned-from-3-471-1717533788-0_dblbig.jpg?resize=1200:*", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 12:01:02", "author": "https://www.buzzfeed.com/about,Michele Bird", "authors": ["https://www.buzzfeed.com/about", "Michele Bird"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.34}